# Monorepo Stability

Retain is a pnpm + Turborepo monorepo (`apps/*`, `packages/*`). Prefer small, reversible changes.

## Scope

- Change only what the task requires. No drive-by refactors or unrelated files.
- Match existing naming, imports (`*.js` extensions in ESM TS), and patterns in neighboring code.
- Do not add business logic to scaffold/health paths unless asked.

## Packages

| Package | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `@retain/api` | Fastify + Mercurius, Shopify OAuth/webhooks |
| `@retain/database` | Prisma schema, client, seed |
| `@retain/shared` | Shared types/constants |
| `@retain/admin` / `@retain/portal` | Vite frontends |
| `@retain/ai` | Python FastAPI (venv under `apps/ai/.venv`) |
| `@retain/webhook-worker` | BullMQ worker |

- Import shared code via workspace packages (`@retain/database`, `@retain/shared`), not deep relative paths across apps.
- After `pnpm install` or schema changes, run `pnpm db:generate` if Prisma client is missing or stale.
- `@prisma/client` is CJS: use `@retain/database`'s exports (`PrismaClient` value + type). Do not reintroduce bare named ESM imports that break under tsx/Node.

## Infra ports (local)

Postgres `5433`, Redis `6380`, ClickHouse `8123` — do not bind default `5432`/`6379` (used by other stacks).

## Secrets

Never commit `.env`. Use `.env.example` templates only.
